
workspace:
	1. The environment shared by all Bazel commands run
	in the same main repository.
	2. (obsolete) The directory tree containing the source files.


repository:
	1. A directory with a WORKSPACE.bazel or WORKSPACE file,
	containing source files to be used in a Bazel build

	see: https://bazel.build/external/overview

package:
	1. A directory containing a BUILD or BUILD.bazel file.
	2. A collection of related files and a specification of how
	they can be used to produce output artifacts.
